\s2 Barnabas vouches for Saul
\p 
\v 26 \w Now|strong="G1161"\w* \w upon|strong="G1519"\w* arriving \w in|strong="G1519"\w* \w Jerusalem|strong="G2419"\w* Saul \w kept|strong="G4100"\w* \w trying|strong="G3985"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w join|strong="G2853"\w* \w himself|strong="G2853"\w* \w to|strong="G1519"\w* \w the|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciples|strong="G3101"\w*;\f + \fr 9:26 \ft I get the impression that he made repeated efforts; after all, he probably had a very good idea of where different groups could be found. Either he didn't know where the apostles were, or lacked the courage to approach them. It was probably after several efforts that Barnabas got wind of what was happening; however, the news doubtless spread through the community quite quickly.\f* \w but|strong="G1161"\w* \w they|strong="G2532"\w* \w were|strong="G1510"\w* \w all|strong="G3956"\w* \w afraid|strong="G5399"\w* \w of|strong="G2532"\w* \w him|strong="G3588"\w*, \w not|strong="G3361"\w* \w believing|strong="G4100"\w* \w that|strong="G3754"\w* \w he|strong="G2532"\w* \w was|strong="G1510"\w* \w a|strong="G2532"\w* \w disciple|strong="G3101"\w*.
